narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned how to effectively respond to feedback and develop my leadership skills.
The core components of leadership and followership.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Course engagement is very strong. I feel that not enough was done with the Turn This Ship Around book later in the semester, but the powerpoints and slides were very helpful in getting the material across to us students.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes. As an AS200 cadet, you will need to take this course and fully understand the material in order to prepare yourself for the Professional Officer Course. Without this class, the fundamentals of leadership and teamwork may not be as well understood by cadets and LLAB/PMT will not be as successful as it is now.
Yes, it is important to have guidance when it comes to various perspectives on leadership.
